org.jtimer

Class Grapher

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.application.Application
      • org.jtimer.Grapher

  • public class Grapher
extends javafx.application.Application
    The object that graphs all the data. For all intents and purposes, this class is a Singleton class and multiple instances of it should not be run. As the behavior may not be as expected.
    Author:
    MagneticZero

      • setGraphTitle

        public void setGraphTitle(java.lang.String graphTitle)
        Sets the grapher title. If the time method is still running it will append a percentage to the end of the title. If the warmup is still running, it will append a warmup tag and a percentage to the end of the title.
        Parameters:
        graphTitle - The title to set it to

      • setProgress

        public void setProgress(java.lang.Double progress,
                        boolean warmup)
        Used to set the progress of the graph so that the user knows that something is actually happening. This is formatted to only 2 decimals places.
        Parameters:
        progress - The progress that has been completed
        warmup - If this is triggered by the warmup

      • setMax

        public void setMax(double max)
        Sets the maximum value that the graph will graph.
        By default this is infinity, I.E. there is no maximum value that the graph will not allow.
        Parameters:
        max - The maximum value

      • setMaxDeviations

        public void setMaxDeviations(double maxDeviations)
        Maximum amount of deviations the graph will show.
        By default this is 2, so data only within 2 standard deviations will be shown. Statisitcally, this means around 95% of the data collected will be shown.
        Parameters:
        maxDeviations - The maximum amount of deviations

      • clearData

        public void clearData()
        This method is used to clear all the data within the graphs. There's really no reason for you to use this method, I use it only for clearing data between tests.

      • getPlots

        public java.util.List<javafx.scene.chart.ScatterChart<java.lang.Number,java.lang.Number>> getPlots()

        Returns:
        A list of plots used by the Grapher

      • finish

        private void finish(boolean bestFit)
        Finishes a graph by:
        • Adding all the data
        • Calculating lines of best fit
        • Limiting the graph view
        • Allows toggling of data
        Parameters:
        bestFit - Whether or not the function of best fit should be calculated

      • prettifyView

        private void prettifyView()
        "Prettifies" all graphs by limiting the view of it to within the max deviations setting standard deviations. Also makes the data points on the graphs a bit smaller since they're too big by default.
        See Also:
        prettifyView(ScatterChart)

      • prettifyView

        private void prettifyView(javafx.scene.chart.ScatterChart<java.lang.Number,java.lang.Number> graph)
        "Prettifies" a graph by limiting the view of it to within the max deviations setting standard deviations. Also makes the data points on the graph a bit smaller since they're too big by default.
        Parameters:
        graph - the graph to "prettify"
